==English==
===Noun===
'''long vowel''' ''(plural:'' long vowels)
# A vowel which is normally pronounced somewhat longer than other vowels (usually around 1½ to double length); represented in the [[IPA]] by the addition of a colon-like symbol, as, /aː/.
# ''(English pronunciation)'' Any of the vowels or [[diphthong]]s resulting from the [[Great Vowel Shift]]'s effect on Middle English's original long vowels, and best exhibited in the names of the vowel letters [[A]], [[E]], [[I]], [[O]], [[U]].  In American lexicography their pronunciation is indicated by a [[macron]], as, ''ē''.

